Rating: 4
I love this recipe. It takes 10 minutes to put together, makes the house smell amazing and is a light, delicious treat. One error in the directions - it says "Beat well" but this is a quickbread and that will *ruin* the cake by developing too much gluten in the flour. Most epicurious fans probably knew this and adjusted naturally, but if you share this recipe with an inexperienced cook, tell them to mix the wet and dry ingredients separately first, combine them and mix just until moist, then add the zest, mix a couple more turns around the bowl and put it in the pan. This process takes 30 seconds longer than the "dump and stir" approach but the cake comes out beautiful and golden every time!

