This easy, delightful quick bread is really a cross between a not too sweet cake and a nut bread. It is great with a cup of coffee or tea, and equally good sliced for breakfast. I put the pine nuts into the batter along with the golden raisins, reserving a few nuts to sprinkle on top of the batter. The lightly lemon flavor with the sweet raisins and the piney flavor of the pine nuts was delightful! I have already made it several times, both for snacking and to put on a brunch buffet. Aside from the task of grating the lemon peel, it is very quick to stir up by hand or with the beater.